name: Ariane 5 ECA | Eutelsat W2M & Hot Bird 9

status.name: Launch Successful
status.description: The launch vehicle successfully inserted its payload(s) into the target orbit(s).

net_precision.name: Second
net_precision.description: The T-0 is accurate to the second.

mission.name: Eutelsat W2M & Hot Bird 9
mission.description: EutelSat W2M is a telecommunications satellite opperated by Afghanistan's Ministry of Communications and Information Technology. It is used to provide communications services to Europe, North Africa and the Middle East. Operating at 16 degrees East. Hotbird 9 is a communications satellite operated by Eutelsat, providing communications to Europe, North Africa and the Middle East. Operating at 13 degrees East.

pad.name: Ariane Launch Area 3
pad.description: ELA-3, is a launch pad and associated facilities at the Centre Spatial Guyanais in French Guiana. ELA-3 was operated by Arianespace as part of the expendable launch system for Ariane 5 launch vehicles.

location.name: Guiana Space Centre, French Guiana
location.description: The Guiana Space Centre is a European spaceport to the northwest of Kourou in French Guiana, a region of France in South America. Kourou is located at a latitude of 5°. In operation since 1968, it is a suitable location for a spaceport because of its equatorial location and open sea to the east.
